## §5 report protocol

### When to use §5 output

- Verify and release when onboarding, help content, and support handoffs are defined
- Launch readiness for success plans, SLAs, and escalation paths
- Post-release when churn signals, feedback loops, and documentation gaps appear

### Phase awareness

- **Strongest:** E–F (Verify, Release) and **post-release** — **high**
- **Moderate:** C–D when in-product guidance and success milestones are designed — **medium**
- **Lighter:** A–B unless customer journey and outcomes are undefined — **low–medium**

### What to inspect

- Onboarding clarity, time-to-value, and milestone definitions
- Support readiness: playbooks, tooling, staffing assumptions
- Feedback loops from customers to product and engineering
- Churn and health indicators tied to actionable interventions
- Documentation quality for self-serve and assisted paths

### Scope boundaries

- **Out of scope:** **code quality** (Software Engineering Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **architecture** decisions (Architecture Versona)
- **Out of scope:** **data engineering** or pipeline design (Big Data Versona)

